To upgrade to a newer upstream commit:
  1. git clone the URL above at the new commit.
  2. Replace storage/include/{crc.h,mmc.h} and storage/src/{crc.c,mmc.c}
     in this directory with the fresh clone's copies (keep this
     VENDORED_COMMIT file and pic8-sdcard/third_party/patches/, update the
     commit hash/date above).
  3. cd to the repo root and run:
       patch -p0 --dry-run < pic8-sdcard/third_party/patches/0001-host-build-compat.patch
     (note: -p0, not -p1 -- the patch's paths already include the
     "pic8-sdcard/" prefix). If it applies cleanly, apply for real (drop
     --dry-run). If a hunk fails, check whether upstream already fixed
     that issue before re-deriving it.
  4. Re-run the host build (cmake -B build && cmake --build build &&
     ctest --test-dir build) and the real xc8-cc compile (see the plan
     doc's Phase 2 findings for the exact flags) before trusting the
     upgrade.
